    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p><p>Meanwhile, combine your<strong> mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!) and <strong>harissa paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> harissa mixture</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-chinese-style-lean-pork-lettuce-boats-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>harissa mixture</strong> and cook for 4 min or until it's beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Cook for a further 4 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-chinese-style-lean-pork-lettuce-boats-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, top, tail, peel and grate your<strong> carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail and grate your <strong>courgette[s]</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-chinese-style-lean-pork-lettuce-boats-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, transfer the<strong> harissa mince</strong> to a clean mixing bowl, reserve the pan</p><p>Add your <strong>soy sauce</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and mix to combine</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-chinese-style-lean-pork-lettuce-boats-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a high heat and once hot, add the <strong>grated</strong> <strong>carrot </strong>and <strong>grated courgette </strong>and cook for an initial 2 min</p><p>Add the <strong>harissa mince</strong> back to the pan, reduce the heat to low and cook for a further 2 min, then remove from the heat and cover to keep warm until serving</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-chinese-style-lean-pork-lettuce-boats-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Separate the<strong> outer leaves</strong> and arrange them on a plate</p><p>Shred the <strong>inner core[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-chinese-style-lean-pork-lettuce-boats-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Stir the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong> through the warmed harissa mince \u2013 this is your <strong>Chinese-style mince</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/speedy-chinese-style-lean-pork-lettuce-boats-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To build your lettuce boats, top each <strong>lettuce leaf</strong> with a spoonful of <strong>basmati</strong> <strong>rice</strong> and some <strong>Chinese-style mince</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>shredded lettuce</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
